race.comment: FIRST EMPIRE (20) hasn't done much wrong with a win and three placings from four starts to commence the career and will strip fitter for that first-up hit-out. Draws the inside marble and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Rates the testing material. KILONOVA (17) has only missed a drum once in five attempts over this six-furlong journey and will be rock-hard fit for this. Looms as the main danger. BLUEPINOT (13) brings southern formlines to the table and should find this assignment a touch easier. Top-three credentials. IMPENDOR (7) has saluted on all going and gets the reliable Dunn/Mallyon combination. In the mix. MOSCOW CIRCUS (14) best of the rest while fresh.
